' Strict-compound effective supply — why a strict multi-sig deploy funds from the
' Split/Join effective supply (the component pair), and the §D2.9 fix: the replay
' recompute keys its strict re-verification + settle-filter on EFFECTIVE supply,
' not the compound pool's RAW presence (which forked play vs replay).
'
' Source of truth for cost-accounting-impl/d2-9-funding-flow.md (Figure G).
'
' Palette:  supply pools / admit mint #C8E6C9 · effective-fold teal #B2DFDB
'   decision amber #FFE082 · fork/reject red #EF9A9A · input orange #FFE0B2
'   conserve/byte-identical green #C8E6C9
'
' Render:  plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/diagrams/strict-compound-effective-supply.puml

@startuml strict-compound-effective-supply
!theme plain
skinparam defaultFontName "sans-serif"
skinparam ArrowColor                     #444444
skinparam ActivityBorderColor            #333333
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor        #FFFFFF
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFE082
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor     #333333
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor            #FFF8E1
skinparam NoteBorderColor                #666666
title Strict compound deploy — fund from effectiveΣ, not raw compound presence (§D2.9)

start
:a strict, compound (multi-sig) deploy\nfunding_sig = And(Ground(pk_l), Ground(pk_r)); <<#FFE0B2>>
:genesis seeds the cosigner wallets\nΣ⟦Ground(pk_l)⟧, Σ⟦Ground(pk_r)⟧ — but NOT\nthe combined Σ⟦And(…)⟧ pool; <<#C8E6C9>>
:effectiveΣ = Σ_compound (absent ⇒ 0) + min(Σ_l, Σ_r)\n(the Split/Join fold); <<#B2DFDB>>

if (what does the recompute key on?) then (OLD — raw compound-pool presence)
  :Σ_compound is ABSENT ⇒ "not present"; <<#EF9A9A>>
  :PLAY admits (it used effectiveΣ),\nbut REPLAY rejects (raw-absent)\n⇒ play / replay FORK; <<#EF9A9A>>
  note right
    The latent pre-§D2.9 bug, exposed once the
    component wallets are genuinely funded.
  end note
  stop
else (§D2.9 — EFFECTIVE supply)
  :effectiveΣ > 0 ⇒ ADMIT;\nsettle from the matched component pair\n(left −= k, right −= k — balanced, P8); <<#C8E6C9>>
  :settle-filter keeps the group iff\n(strict ∨ present(own pool)) —\nmirrors the play-side early-admit exactly; <<#C8E6C9>>
  :PLAY debit map == REPLAY recompute\n(byte-identical; non-strict unchanged); <<#C8E6C9>>
  note right
    effective_supply_with(raw, decompositions)
    is the already-proven Split/Join algebra
    (CAJoinConservation) applied at replay —
    no new proof obligation.
  end note
  stop
endif

legend left
| Color | Meaning |
| <#FFE0B2> orange | the strict compound deploy (input) |
| <#C8E6C9> mint | supply pools / admit / conserve |
| <#B2DFDB> teal | the effectiveΣ fold |
| <#FFE082> amber | decision (which key?) |
| <#EF9A9A> red | the raw-presence fork (pre-§D2.9 bug) |
endlegend

@enduml
